 Prepare cup(s). Set up wicks inside clean teacups by placing the wick in between two wooden skewer sticks and taping the ends. Place sticks with wick over the top of the cup so that the wick is standing in the middle of the cup. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Make-Vintage-Teacup-Candles-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Vintage-Teacup-Candles-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Make-Vintage-Teacup-Candles-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Vintage-Teacup-Candles-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fair_use">Fair Use</a> (screenshot)<br>
